get.description:
Identity stores to be used for Central NAC.
These stores can be configured for Identity providers like Azure, Microsoft, Okta and local user or MAC based stores.
They can be referenced in authentication profiles and authorization policies and used for authentication and authorization.
Identity stores must be configured with default query parameters.

post.description:
Identity store to be used for Central NAC.
This store can be configured for Identity providers like Azure, Microsoft, Okta and local user or MAC based stores.
It can be referenced in authentication profiles and authorization policies and used for authentication and authorization.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: Unique immutable identifier for identity store.

delete.description:
Identity store to be used for Central NAC.
This store can be configured for Identity providers like Azure, Microsoft, Okta and local user or MAC based stores.
It can be referenced in authentication profiles and authorization policies and used for authentication and authorization.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: Unique immutable identifier for identity store.

delete_object_type.name: object_type
delete_object_type.description: LOCAL - To delete local objects. SHARED - To delete shared objects. Default - Defaults to SHARED if not provided

delete_scope_id.name: scope_id
delete_scope_id.description: Scope at which local object needs to be deleted. Mandatory if object_type = LOCAL. Should not be provided for object_type = SHARED.

delete_persona.name: persona
delete_persona.description: Persona for which the local object needs to be deleted. Mandatory if object_type = LOCAL. Should not be provided for object_type = SHARED.

post_object_type.name: object_type
post_object_type.description: LOCAL - To create local objects. SHARED - To create shared objects. Default - Defaults to SHARED if not provided

post_scope_id.name: scope_id
post_scope_id.description: Scope at which local object needs to be created. Mandatory if object_type = LOCAL. Should not be provided for object_type = SHARED.

post_persona.name: persona
post_persona.description: Persona for which the local object needs to be created. Mandatory if object_type = LOCAL. Should not be provided for object_type = SHARED.

patch_object_type.name: object_type
patch_object_type.description: LOCAL - To update local objects. SHARED - To update shared objects. Default - Defaults to SHARED if not provided

patch_scope_id.name: scope_id
patch_scope_id.description: Scope at which local object needs to be updated. Mandatory if object_type = LOCAL. Should not be provided for object_type = SHARED.

patch_persona.name: persona
patch_persona.description: Persona for which the local object needs to be updated. Mandatory if object_type = LOCAL. Should not be provided for object_type = SHARED.

get_object_type.name: object_type
get_object_type.description: Retrieves LOCAL or SHARED or both(default) configuration objects.

get_scope_id.name: scope_id
get_scope_id.description: Configuration at a given scope. Mandatory for view_type = LOCAL.

get_persona.name: persona
get_persona.description: Filters configuration specific to given persona type. If not provided and view_type = LOCAL, then defaults to all persona.

effective.name: effective
effective.description: True - Returns effective configuration (i.e hierarchically merged configuration). False - Returns committed configuration at a given scope.

detailed.name: detailed
detailed.description: True - Includes annotations in the returned json to indicate the type of object, scope, and persona. False - Returns only config objects without annotations.

view_type.name: view_type
view_type.description: LIBRARY - Returns shared objects in library. For LIBRARY, all other parameters listed below, except 'detailed' , will be ignored. LOCAL - Returns configurations for a scope and one or more persona based on parameters below.

store.description:
Identity store to be used for Central NAC.
This store can be configured for Identity providers like Azure, Microsoft, Okta and local user or MAC based stores.
It can be referenced in authentication profiles and authorization policies and used for authentication and authorization.

x-enumDescriptions.GOOGLE_SOCIAL: Sign-in with a Google account (social login).
x-enumDescriptions.FACEBOOK: Sign-in with a Facebook account (social login).

x-enumDescriptions.OPENID_CONNECT: Sign-in with an OpenID Connect provider.
x-enumDescriptions.X: Sign-in with an X (formerly Twitter) account (social login).

ANY.description: Any of local or shared config object.

ArubaCdaIdentityStore_OauthCommon.description: OAuth credentials required by any identity store providers to identify the Cloud Authentication and Policy application.

client-id.description: OAuth client ID is issued by identity store provider and is used to identify the Cloud Authentication and Policy application.

client-secret.x-typeDescription:
A custom derived type for special use cases. This type takes a plaintext password and uses
Vault's 3rd party API to encrypt the password. The intended use case is to encrypt and store
customer credentials which will be used later to login to 3rd party services.
client-secret.description: OAuth client secret is issued by the identity store provider and is used to authenticate the Cloud Authentication and Policy application.

microsoft.description: Microsoft Entra ID store configuration. To configure Microsoft Entra ID, id-store-type field should be set to MICROSOFT.

google.description: Google Workspace store configuration. To configure Google Workspace, id-store-type field should be set to GOOGLE.

customer-id.description: Customer ID for Google Workspace account.

admin-email.description: Admin email for Google Workspace account.

ArubaCdaIdentityStore_GoogleServiceAccou.description: Represents fields from the Google Developers service account JSON key file.

type.description: This field maps to the 'type' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

project-id.description: This field maps to the 'project_id' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

private-key-id.description: This field maps to the 'private_key_id' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

private-key.x-typeDescription:
A custom derived type for special use cases. This type takes a plaintext password and uses
Vault's 3rd party API to encrypt the password. The intended use case is to encrypt and store
customer credentials which will be used later to login to 3rd party services.
private-key.description: This field maps to the 'private_key' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

client-email.description: This field maps to the 'client_email' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

service-client-id.description: This field maps to the 'client_id' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

auth-uri.description: This field maps to the 'auth_uri' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

token-uri.description: This field maps to the 'token_uri' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

auth-provider-x509-cert-url.description: This field maps to the 'auth_provider_x509_cert_url' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

client-x509-cert-url.description: This field maps to the 'client_x509_cert_url' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

universe-domain.description: This field maps to the 'universe_domain' field in the Google Developers service account JSON file.

okta.description: Okta Workforce Identity store configuration. To configure Okta Workforce Identity, id-store-type field should be set to OKTA.

domain.description: Okta domain is also called Okta URL. Okta domain can be obtained from the Okta Workforce Identity Cloud Administration Console.

service-client-id.description: This maps to the client ID in Client credential section of the Okta Workforce Identity Cloud administration console.

service-client-secret.x-typeDescription:
A custom derived type for special use cases. This type takes a plaintext password and uses
Vault's 3rd party API to encrypt the password. The intended use case is to encrypt and store
customer credentials which will be used later to login to 3rd party services.
service-client-secret.description: Service Client Secret are obtained from the Okta Workforce Identity Cloud administration console.

ArubaCdaIdentityStore_GoogleSocialConfig.description: Additional configuration for a Google (social login) identity store.

google-social.description: Google (social login) identity store configuration. To configure Google (social login) Workforce Identity, id-store-type field should be set to GOOGLE_SOCIAL.

hosted-domain.x-typeDescription: A domain name (as supported by Cloud Guest) according to RFC 952 and RFC 1123.
hosted-domain.description: The google hosted domain that users must be members of, to allow authorization

ArubaCdaIdentityStore_FacebookConfig.description: Additional configuration for a Facebook social login identity store.

facebook.description: Facebook social login identity store configuration. To configure Facebook social login, id-store-type field should be set to FACEBOOK.

ArubaCdaIdentityStore_LinkedinConfig.description: Additional configuration for a LinkedIn social login identity store.

linkedin.description: LinkedIn social login identity store configuration. To configure LinkedIn social login, id-store-type field should be set to LINKEDIN.

ArubaCdaIdentityStore_OpenidConnectConfi.description: Additional configuration for an OpenID Connect provider.

openid-connect.description: OpenID Connect identity store configuration. To configure an OpenID Connect provider, id-store-type field should be set to OPENID_CONNECT.

authorization-url.x-typeDescription:
An ASCII-encoded Uniform Resource Locator (URL) as defined
in RFC 3986, section 1.1.3
authorization-url.description: The Authorization Endpoint URL to which the user will be redirected for authentication

token-url.x-typeDescription:
An ASCII-encoded Uniform Resource Locator (URL) as defined
in RFC 3986, section 1.1.3
token-url.description: The Token Endpoint URL from which the ID token will be retrieved (after successful authentication)

ArubaCdaIdentityStore_XConfig.description: Additional configuration for an X, formerly Twitter, social login identity store.

x.description: X social login identity store configuration. To configure X social login, id-store-type field should be set to X.
